				<font face="verdana" size="3"><a name="16">Alan Vancouvering on pets & related issue's</a></font><br>
				<font face="verdana" size="2">
				<b><a href="mailto:catalyst@everlore.com">Catalyst</b></a>
				[11/30/2000-1:18:24 PM]</font>
				&nbsp;<a href="Comments.asp?ID=287528"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Comments[2]</font></a>
				<p>
				<font face="verdana" size="2"><Blockquote>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/035388.html">Pet Clarification Post</a></B><P>

<I>Let me summarize, for convenience sake, the changes that we have made to pets over the course of the last few patches.<P>

Pets wielding weapons will now proc with those weapons just as frequently as a player character with that weapon and the same stats. This has reduced the frequency of weapon procs from pets. To make this change we simply removed an artificial multiplier to pet proc chances, no stats or attributes were changed.<P>

Pets wielding the Sword of Runes will proc with that sword as often as they do with any other procing weapon, but it will only proc against its intended target, summoned creatures.<P>

Magician and necromancer pets (and because they use the same spells, shadowknight pets as well) now have the ability to duel wield without a weapon, if they are powerful enough. This will happen with some regularity with pets cast from 39th level (52nd for shadowknights) spells and above.<P>

No other changes to the duel wielding ability of any other pets was changed. This ability was not given to any other pet because magicians and necromancers are primary pet classes, the others are not.<P>

Alan</I><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

Bowynn wrote: "You want a hostile tone? Keep avoiding this."<P>

<B>Be hostile if that helps you, I suppose. Just stick within the board guidelines and we'll be fine. But I have answered this. I thought I answered it very clearly previously. Enchanters did not get nerfed. They were not ignored. It was decided that only the two mentioned pet types would get the dual wielding without weapons ability.<P>

I'd be really interested to see if any other enchanters feel as you do…</B><P>

Lady_Melkore wrote: "So the specter level 59 necro pet will be duel weilding/double attacking?? Is that what i heard"<P>

<B>Spectres come with a big ol' two-handed scythe… Yet somehow they will still be dual wielding. Don't ask me how…<P>

Alan</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

P_Chamberlain wrote: "Remove SOR proc on non-sommoned - Fix/nerf..
Lower proc rate - Fix/nerf...
Remove need for wep to dual attack - Fix/nerf...
Lower pet dex - Fix/nerf...."<P>

<B>Two clarifications on your list.<P>

1) Removing the need for a weapon to dual wield is, by no stretch of the imagination, a nerf.<BR>
2) We did not change any pet attributes.</B><P>

Inn_DB said: "Pets after level 39 can duel wield. 
before the patch, pets before that level could duel wield. So really the pet does not have the duel wield skill it use to have?"<P>

<B>I'll restate it, maybe that will help. Nothing at all was changed about the way pets use weapons. We added the ability for some pets to dual wield without a weapon. If your pet could dual wield with a weapon before, it still can. It just might be able to dual wield without one now.<P>

Alan</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/035577.html">Question for Absor...</a></B><P>

Absor, I've been playing with a pet class only for the past 4-5 weeks. And reading the lvl's of the pets, it seems that we could always get a pet that was blue/white/yellow from the spell lvl.
I mean. Lvl 8 spell, pets are lvl 7-9. Lvl 12 spell pets are lvl 11-13. Looking in Everlore, seems like that's been the case all along.<P>

Well, I hit lvl 12 with my Necro right around your patch a few weeks ago. Got my new spells, and new pet. Well, After going through a few stack of bones... never got a White or Yellow pet. Now that I'm lvl 14, I started to get Green pets... Meaning that it is a lvl 9 pet.<P>

<B>I'll see what I can find out about the history of pet levels relative to the spell level. But I'm pretty sure that pet levels haven't been changed lately.<P>

Alan</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/035358.html">This patch officially rocks.</a></B><P>

Thank you, VI, for doing everything right this time. 
Execpt for a few people losing their guildtags, everything works as advertised. and nearest and dearest to my heart, the pets are restored to their former tanking ability. The last patch weakened them severely, and now besides dualwielding without weapons as promised (I can chuck my sacks of daggers AT LAST!) my pet was tanking for me as good as ever, surviving fights with 90 hitters at about half health as he used to, and holding off a 2 mob pull until I could get crowd control down, as he used to do. Thank you, VI dev, for restoring my faith.<P>

<B>We really didn't change anything about pets except the rate at which they proc with weapons. Not in the last patch, and not in this one...</B><P>

"Then how come no word to us while we posted 90000 times that they did?"<P>

<B>Well, I did tell you that we hadn't changed anything. I didn't think it was necessary to say it over and over again.<P>

I talked to some personal friends that play mages (and don't read these boards), and they told me things were as usual, except for the procing thing. I talked to everyone here a few dozen times, they told me nothing had changed except the procs for weapons…<P>

I was looking for something else to do, other than tell you guys over and over again that nothing else had changed…<P>

I don't know if it was a 'placebo effect' thing or if there really was some sort of temporary bug. All the evidence that I have from internal and personal resources tells me it was never broken. Many of you tell me otherwise.<P>

*shrug*<P>

I'm just glad that, whatever it was, it's all better now.<P>

Alan</B><P>

